I need to identify the specific line items and values of profit or loss retained in the entity rather than distributed to shareholders.

Looking at the balance sheet, the line item that represents retained profits is "Retained Earnings". This account shows the cumulative profits that have been kept in the business instead of being paid out as dividends.

In the balance sheet:
- The initial value of Retained Earnings as of 2023-12-31 is 0.00
- The end value of Retained Earnings as of 2024-02-05 is 1903401.82

This indicates that during this period, the company retained $1,903,401.82 of profit in the business rather than distributing it to shareholders.
